parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Propulsion Power Reduction and Loss of Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of propulsion power and acceleration can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while in motion, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Error messages "Propulsion Power Reduced" or "Shift to Park" appear on the dashboard
sudden loss of acceleration
inability to shift gears
vehicle stalls or loses power while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Shift to Park Message and Failure to Recognize Park Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to recognize the park gear can cause the vehicle to remain running and energized after the driver thinks they have turned it off, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Error message "Shift to Park" appears on the dashboard
vehicle fails to recognize park gear
vehicle remains running and energized after driver thinks they have turned it off
difficulty turning off the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Sudden loss of acceleration
inability to shift gears
vehicle stalls or loses power while in motion
error messages related to transmission failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly shift into park can cause the vehicle to remain in a running state, posing a risk of accidents, injuries, or fires. Additionally, the inability to turn off the vehicle can lead to inconvenience, frustration, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a message "Attention Needed: Shift to Park" or "Shift to Park" accompanied by audio alerts
the vehicle cannot be turned off reliably
the vehicle requires multiple attempts to shift into park
the vehicle will not shut off until the shift handle is jiggled or the vehicle is restarted and re-set to park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery control module can cause the vehicle to stop running, leaving the driver stranded in traffic, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stops running
the battery control module is defective
the vehicle is unable to start or shut down properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of remote detection can cause inconvenience and frustration, potentially leading to safety risks if the vehicle is not properly secured.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "NO REMOTE DETECTED" message
even when the remote is present in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the vehicle may not respond properly to braking inputs.
symptoms: The vehicle slows down only slightly when the brake pedal is applied
despite the wheels still rotating
the vehicle does not stop properly
the airbags deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shift to park error can cause the vehicle to not shut off, leading to safety concerns and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The "shift to park" error message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle does not shut off even when the shift lever is in park
the error message persists despite wiggling the shift lever
the error message clears after restarting the vehicle and shifting in and out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The non-compliance with brake system fastener protocols can lead to safety risks, including brake failure, and compromise the reliability of the vehicle.
symptoms: None reported
as this is a concern about dealer service compliance with factory service manuals and potential safety risks.
